  "response": "Yes, it is possible for the public to watch an ISRO satellite launch from a safe distance at the Satish Dhawan Space Centre in Sriharikota. ISRO provides viewing opportunities for interested spectators through a public viewing gallery that has been specifically constructed for this purpose. To attend a launch, you typically need to register in advance via the official ISRO website, as the number of spectators is limited. It's important to check the availability, specific guidelines, and any COVID-19 related restrictions ISRO might have in place prior to planning your visit.",
